issue_7198_body.text:
Requests depends explicitly on `charset_normalizer>=2,<4`. However when `chardet` happens to be installed, it is used instead, leading to observably different behavior when a response without explicit charset is parsed.

## Expected Result

`requests` should prefer its own explicit dependency `charset_normalizer`, which by virtue of being an explicit dependency, would be assumed to always be installed.

## Actual Result

`requests` prefers to use `chardet`, if it happens to be installed.

## Reproduction Steps

Without `chardet` installed; requests detects `utf-8` encoding for a URL on PyPI:

```
python -m venv /tmp/req1
/tmp/req1/bin/python -m pip install requests
/tmp/req1/bin/python -c '
  import sys, requests;
  R = requests.get("https://pypi.org/integrity/pyjwt/2.11.0/pyjwt-2.11.0-py3-none-any.whl/provenance");
  print(R.apparent_encoding, file=sys.stderr);
  print(R.text)' | jq -r '.attestation_bundles[0].attestations[0].verification_material.transparency_entries[0].inclusionProof.checkpoint.envelope'
```

This outputs, after the pip output, an em-dash:

```
utf-8
rekor.sigstore.dev - 1193050959916656506
751473133
9tPKS6jjzjerKz/8vzroaKEdttCo+JIEgDtu3tCqxks=

— rekor.sigstore.dev wNI9ajBEAiA3l389wnJX5QxAcGmYhIT69L7HsG27tL37YvRCrZ3HkgIgOH1KOC/4/jfpY3YRvG6z+jGkloB8MUCwHqNYOn17h/0=
```

With `chardet` installed, `requests` detects `Windows-1252` encoding for a URL on PyPI:

```
